Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/inSeries
Object: Relates the series position of a work to a series in which that work appears.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/toManifestation
Object: Relates a revision to the manifestation which immediately follows that revision.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Series
Object: A specialised form of collection, allowing works to be placed in an order.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/hasFormat
Object: Relates an expression to the format taken by that expression. Different expressions of the same work may have different formats.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Manifestation
Object: A manifestation of an expression of a work, allowing for multiple versions of an expression over time, for example: an edition of a book, or a remastered audio file of a podcast episode.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/collectionPartOfCollection
Object: Relates a collection to a wider collection it forms part of, for example: a collection of works on health policy generally formed of collections of works concerned with particular areas of health policy.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/manifestationHasFocus
Object: Relates a manifestation to the focus area of that manifestation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/hasContribution
Object: Relates a manifestation to a contribution. Contributors to a work may differ across different manifestations of that work.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/hasGeographicScope
Object: Denotes the geographic scope of a work, the scope being a geographic place.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/partOfCollection
Object: Includes a work within a collection, as a part of that collection.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/referenceNumber
Object: The reference number of a work.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Work
Object: A distinct intellectual creation, similar to a work as defined in FRBR.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/inSeriesPosition
Object: Relates a work to the position that work has within a series.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/minimumReadingAge
Object: The minimum reading age for a manifestation of a work.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Contribution
Object: A contribution by an agent, for example: by a person or by a corporate author.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/SeriesPosition
Object: The position of a work within a series of works.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/manifestationOf
Object: Relates a manifestation of an expression to that expression. An expression may have more than one manifestation. A manifestation has a single expression.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Place
Object: A place named in a geography.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/hasAttachment
Object: Relates a manifestation to a file..

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/hasRevisionType
Object: Relates a revision to the type of that revision.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Focus
Object: A focus area for a manifestation or collection of works. Allows us to point at any modelled thing as a focus area, for example: a committee or a bill.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/
Object: A model informed by FRBR - describing works, collections of works, their expressions and manifestations.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Format
Object: The format taken by the expression of a work, for example: the format of the expression of a podcast episode - as an audio file, or as a text transcript.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/publishedAt
Object: The date and time of the publication of a manifestation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Revision
Object: A revision from a preceding to a following manifestation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/File
Object: A file associated with a manifestation of a work, for example: a spreadsheet, a PDF or a Word document.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/hasRevisionDescription
Object: The description of a revision, for example: “updated to include recent legislation”.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/expressionOf
Object: Relates an expression to the work as expressed. An expression is of a single work. A work has one or more expressions.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/collectionHasFocus
Object: Relates a collection to the focus area of that collection.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/RevisionType
Object: The type of a revision, for example: a major update or a minor update.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/fromManifestation
Object: Relates a revision to the manifestation which immediately precedes that revision.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/mediaType
Object: The media type of a file.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/takesEditorialForm
Object: Relates a work to an editorial form.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/scope
Object: The scope of a work, for example: the scope of a POST briefing.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/Expression
Object: A work may be realised - as an expression - having more than one format, for example: a podcast episode made available as an audio file and as a text transcript.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/record/EditorialForm
Object: The editorial form of a work, for example: a report, an article, a transcript, or the minutes of a meeting.
